02:56:53,687 --> 02:56:55,147
I'll never let go.

2043
02:56:55,480 --> 02:56:56,732
I promise.

2044
02:57:39,816 --> 02:57:41,651
Come about!

2045
02:58:03,006 --> 02:58:06,843
Fifteen hundred people went into the sea

2046
02:58:07,177 --> 02:58:10,222
when <i>Titanic </i>sank from under us.

2047
02:58:12,057 --> 02:58:15,227
There were twenty boats floating nearby,

2048
02:58:16,395 --> 02:58:18,688
and only one came back.

2049
02:58:20,524 --> 02:58:21,608
One.

2050
02:58:23,360 --> 02:58:26,029
Six were saved from the water,

2051
02:58:26,530 --> 02:58:28,198
myself included.

2052
02:58:29,366 --> 02:58:30,659
Six,

2053
02:58:31,868 --> 02:58:33,912
out of fifteen hundred.

2054
02:58:37,040 --> 02:58:38,375
Afterward,

2055
02:58:39,543 --> 02:58:41,545
the seven hundred people in the boats

2056
02:58:42,295 --> 02:58:44,423
had nothing to do but wait.

2057
02:58:46,049 --> 02:58:47,717
Wait to die.

2058
02:58:48,218 --> 02:58:49,761
Wait to live.

2059
02:58:50,929 --> 02:58:53,098
Wait for an absolution

2060
02:58:53,598 --> 02:58:55,434
that would never come.

2061
02:59:59,623 --> 03:00:02,042
Sir, I don't think you'll find any
of your people down here.

2062
03:00:02,209 --> 03:00:03,668
It's all steerage.

2063
03:00:06,630 --> 03:00:10,175
His hair is reddish brown,
reddish brown, reddish brown.

2064
03:00:10,300 --> 03:00:11,676
White beard.

2065
03:00:12,135 --> 03:00:13,762
Isn't there another passenger list?

2066
03:00:13,845 --> 03:00:14,971
There is no other list.

2067
03:00:15,096 --> 03:00:16,556
Perhaps he's on another ship.

2068
03:00:16,848 --> 03:00:18,975
We're doing all we can, ma'am.
I'm so sorry.

2069
03:00:41,998 --> 03:00:44,668
 <i>That's the last time I ever saw him.</i> 

2070
03:00:45,168 --> 03:00:48,672
 <i>He married, of course,</i> 
 <i>and inherited his millions.</i> 

2071
03:00:49,339 --> 03:00:52,842
 <i>But the Crash of '29 </i> 
 <i>hit his interests hard,</i> 

2072
03:00:53,176 --> 03:00:55,595
 <i>and he put a pistol in</i> 
 <i>his mouth that year.</i> 

2073
03:00:56,054 --> 03:00:57,889
Or so I read.

2074
03:01:10,694 --> 03:01:12,112
Can I take your name please, love?

2075
03:01:15,198 --> 03:01:16,533
Dawson.

2076
03:01:18,702 --> 03:01:20,203
Rose Dawson.

2077
03:01:21,538 --> 03:01:22,706
Thank you.

2078
03:01:29,713 --> 03:01:31,798
We never found anything on Jack.

2079
03:01:32,007 --> 03:01:33,925
There's no record of him at all.

2080
03:01:34,551 --> 03:01:36,928
No, there wouldn't be, would there?

2081
03:01:37,262 --> 03:01:39,973
And I've never spoken of him until now.

2082
03:01:40,724 --> 03:01:42,100
Not to anyone.

2083
03:01:42,934 --> 03:01:44,936
Not even your grandfather.

2084
03:01:45,270 --> 03:01:49,232
A woman's heart is a
deep ocean of secrets.

2085
03:01:50,066 --> 03:01:53,737
But now you know there was
a man named Jack Dawson,

2086
03:01:54,070 --> 03:01:56,072
and that he saved me

2087
03:01:56,406 --> 03:01:59,743
in every way that a person can be saved.

2088
03:02:01,745 --> 03:02:04,414
I don't even have a picture of him.

2089
03:02:06,916 --> 03:02:10,754
He exists now only in my memory.

2090
03:02:15,592 --> 03:02:19,137
Keldysh,<i> Mir 2 on our way to the surface.</i>

2091
03:02:35,612 --> 03:02:38,365
 <i>I was saving this for when</i> 
 <i>I found the diamond.</i> 

2092
03:02:47,791 --> 03:02:49,292
I'm sorry.

2093
03:02:51,961 --> 03:02:53,463
Three years

2094
03:02:54,130 --> 03:02:56,800
I've thought of nothing except <i>Titanic.</i>

2095
03:02:57,634 --> 03:02:59,469
But I never got it.

2096
03:03:02,597 --> 03:03:04,516
I never let it in.
